This paper deals with the edge unfolding of convex caps, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of data structures and graph theory, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GR (Graph Theory) as likely sub-categories. The paper also involves combinatorial analysis, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves practical applications of the theoretical results, which suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as a possible sub-category.
